  <prompt>
    Migrate the 2 Pattern B BFF consumers from hardcoded playbook lookups to `IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync` calls per spec FR-1R-05. The 2 consumers are `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` (chat-summarize) and `AppOnlyAnalysisService` (email-analysis — the latter still contains the 2 const stable-IDs flagged in task 027 exit gate evidence as Pattern B execution-path consts). Each service receives `IConsumerRoutingService` via constructor injection (Scoped lifetime). One integration test per service confirms identical behavior post-migration vs the Phase 1 baseline. Final grep proves zero hardcoded playbook GUIDs remain in these 2 services.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in chat-routing layer + Phase 1 stable-code migration history + the 2026-06-22 task 027 exit-gate evidence trail (Pattern B execution-path consts at `AppOnlyAnalysisService.cs:46,1068`).</role>

  <goal>
    Both Pattern B consumers (`SessionSummarizeOrchestrator`, `AppOnlyAnalysisService`) resolve their playbook target via `IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync` from the `sprk_playbookconsumer` Dataverse table seeded by 028b. `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` uses the `chat-summarize` consumer type (FR-26 / FR-30 invariants preserved per task 015 evidence). `AppOnlyAnalysisService` uses the `email-analysis` consumer type and the 2 const stable-IDs flagged in task 027 (at `AppOnlyAnalysisService.cs:46,1068`) are removed. 2 integration tests (one per service) pass against the migrated codepath. Final `Grep` for hardcoded playbook GUIDs in these 2 files returns zero.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec §"Phase 1R" FR-1R-05. Pattern B consumers were the secondary group identified in the §1.7 Stable-ID migration — they previously held the playbook lookup as a hardcoded constant (GUID literal or string code) rather than reading from `WorkspaceOptions.*PlaybookId`. Task 027 exit-gate evidence (`notes/handoffs/027-phase-1-exit-gate-evidence.md`) confirmed the 2 remaining `const Guid.Parse(...)` declarations at `AppOnlyAnalysisService.cs:46,1068` are the canonical Pattern B execution-path consts. Phase 1 design intentionally left these in place (task 020 design decision) pending the FR-1R routing infrastructure. With `IConsumerRoutingService` available (task 028a) and seed records in place (task 028b), this task removes them. `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` is FR-26 / FR-30 critical path (chat-summarize first per Phase 1 task 015) — its behavior must remain identical to the Phase 1 baseline. `AppOnlyAnalysisService` is the email-analysis app-only execution path used by the Outlook ribbon Email Analysis playbook.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Routing/IConsumerRoutingService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Routing/ConsumerRoutingService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SessionSummarizeOrchestrator.cs</file>
