    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-1R-05">Both Pattern B consumers migrate to `IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync`; final grep returns zero hardcoded playbook GUIDs in these 2 services.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Stays in `Services/Ai/` boundary; no CRUD-code violations.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task BFF publish-size measurement; report delta vs current baseline (~45.65 MB).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">`IConsumerRoutingService` injected via ctor; no `IServiceProvider.GetService&lt;T&gt;()` in endpoint signatures.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">`ResolveAsync` honors 5-min TTL per-tenant cache from task 028a — consumers MUST NOT add a second cache layer.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">`SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` FR-26 / FR-30 invariants preserved per Phase 1 task 015 evidence — chat-summarize routing behavior unchanged.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">`AppOnlyAnalysisService` removes the 2 const stable-IDs at `:46` and `:1068` flagged by task 027 exit-gate evidence — these are the canonical Pattern B execution-path consts.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Test update obligation (CLAUDE.md §10) — add/update one integration test per migrated consumer; existing Phase 1 tests remain unchanged or are extended in place.</constraint>
  </constraints>

