  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `IConsumerRoutingService.cs` from task 028a output to confirm the final method signature + DI registration lifetime (Scoped). Read `notes/handoffs/027-phase-1-exit-gate-evidence.md` to confirm the 2 const sites at `AppOnlyAnalysisService.cs:46,1068`.</step>
    <step order="2">Read `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator.cs` end-to-end; identify the current hardcoded `chat-summarize` lookup mechanism (whether typed-options `WorkspaceOptions.ChatSummarizePlaybookCode` style or string literal). Confirm via Grep across `WorkspaceOptions.cs`.</step>
    <step order="3">Migrate `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator`: inject `IConsumerRoutingService` via ctor; replace the existing chat-summarize lookup with `await _consumerRouting.ResolveAsync("chat-summarize", ct: ct)`; preserve FR-26 / FR-30 invariants (signature unchanged; routing behavior identical to Phase 1 task 015 baseline). Update existing tests + add one integration test asserting identical behavior pre/post migration.</step>
    <step order="4">Read `AppOnlyAnalysisService.cs:46` and `AppOnlyAnalysisService.cs:1068` to confirm the 2 const Guid declarations. Note the call sites in the file that consume each const.</step>
    <step order="5">Migrate `AppOnlyAnalysisService`: inject `IConsumerRoutingService` via ctor; replace the 2 const Guid declarations + their call sites with `await _consumerRouting.ResolveAsync("email-analysis", ct: ct)`. Confirm the routing context (if any tenant-or-environment selection logic existed) is handled by the routing table's `sprk_environment` column rather than C# branches. Add one integration test asserting identical behavior to the Phase 1 baseline.</step>
    <step order="6">Wire DI: confirm each service registration in its module file (e.g., `Services/Ai/AiModule.cs` or per-service module) takes the `IConsumerRoutingService` dependency cleanly; ensure no asymmetric-registration anti-pattern per CLAUDE.md §10 / `bff-extensions.md` §F.1.</step>
    <step order="7">Run the targeted test suites: `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~SessionSummarizeOrchestrator|FullyQualifiedName~AppOnlyAnalysisService"`. Confirm both new integration tests pass + existing tests pass.</step>
    <step order="8">`Grep` over `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SessionSummarizeOrchestrator.cs` and `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/AppOnly/AppOnlyAnalysisService.cs` for `Guid.Parse("` and inline GUID literals (regex `\b[0-9a-fA-F]{8}-[0-9a-fA-F]{4}`). Expect zero hits.</step>
    <step order="9">Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` then `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`. Measure compressed publish size; record absolute size + delta vs current baseline (~45.65 MB) per ADR-029 / CLAUDE.md §10.</step>
    <step order="10">9.5 quality gates — invoke `code-review` skill + `adr-check` skill. Resolve any findings before marking task complete.</step>
    <step order="11">Write `notes/handoffs/028d-pattern-b-migration-evidence.md` with: per-service diff summary, integration test pass/fail counts, grep evidence (zero hardcoded GUIDs), publish-size delta, and verification that the 2 task-027-flagged const sites are removed.</step>
    <step order="12">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 028d → ✅; current-task.md → ready for 028e (after 028c also lands).</step>
  </steps>

